> hello mark  These weren't the best motors. H number on case with 8mm
> oil pump studs.  had major problems cracking cases and head studs
> pulling. I think the alloy mix was weaker on these and B cases. You
> can linebore them and install case savers and get some use out of
> them. You would be better off using a 73 and up case as they came with
> the factory installed case savers and were stronger cases. The best
> ones are out of the FI bugs but they don't have the holes for mounting
> the mech. fuel pump. Bob(Boston engines) donald preferrs these for
> building Zambonia motors. later  mark dearing
